The paper deals with the formalization of different types of induction, which is a topic that is relevant to several subfields of computer science. The use of well-founded semantics and logic programming suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the application of induction to artificial intelligence, which could make it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of induction over well-founded sets suggests that the paper could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper's focus on modularity could make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
